  "doc_id": "40906",
  "text": "Fasting blood samples were collected to measure serum PCSK9 levels in all 600 subjects. Serum PCSK9 concentration was measured by a sandwich ELISA assay as previously described [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Briefly, 96-well plates were pre-coated with anti-PCSK9 antibody overnight, then incubated with standard recombinant PCSK9 protein or human serum samples, HRP labeled anti-PCSK9 antibody, development substrate and stop solution were accordingly incubated. Lastly, the absorbance was detected at 450 nm. The limit of quantification was 1 ng/ml. The intra-assay and inter-assay coefficient of variation (CV) was 7.9% and 10.2%, respectively.",
